# Convert "*.pem" to "*.ppk" to connect ec2 machine in AWS 

Steps:

1. open putty gen
2. conversion --> import key(Click on Load) --> select 'your keypair'
3. choose SSH-2 instead of SSH-1 for type of key to generate
4. click on 'save private key' button
5. close puttygen
6. open putty.exe
7. host : your public dns on AWS
8. on category panel select SSH --> auth --> browse private keys --> select your .ppk file
9. click 'open' button
10. login as : ubuntu
11. have fun

The key is on step 3, you save it as SSH-2.
